        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        5 Stars
        You know how, cool - great tent!
        The inflatable camping tent from DanCoom is nice, very big, high, quick to set up. If you know how... but of course the writer doesn't read instructions, which often goes well. But I managed it too. I saw that it really only needed to be inflated from one port and can be quickly deflated with the other port ，Simply close the 2nd valve before inflating. Now and then lift a leg, then it stands up straight. I think it takes less than 2 minutes to set up. The pump is good. The zippers are very good and smooth-running without snagging. The windows also open well and can be opened and fixed easily. The floor is hard-wearing. The awning is also very large. Four people can sit in it. Sleeping is safe for 4 people. I am 6 feet tall and can stand in the middle without bumping into the roof.I am delighted with the tent.

        Quality is very deceiving as stated. After set up ( brand new out of the box! )about 2 hours later it started to rain then got windy. My tent got flooded and while trying to scoop water out, the tent started deflating and collapsed entirely. To be honest, tents sold at Walmart has better quality for hundreds less. As hyped up the advertisements says about this inflatable tent, it’s not hyped up as it says nor worth the money. If it wasn’t for my soaked air bed still inside, it would have completely fallen to the ground! Such a big disappointment and disaster my family and I endured!
